   [vertrule.gif] Outreach and Education banner image
   USGS Visitor's Center - The Visitor's Center is an extension of the
   Rolla Earth Science Information Center (ESIC) and houses demonstrations
   and exhibits focusing on many of the activities, products, and services
   provided by the USGS. A visitor can view some of the latest
   technologies that are being developed at MCMC, as well as other USGS
   offices throughout the nation. The Visitor's Center is used as a
   facility for conducting educational programs and hands-on activities.
   Selected USGS brochures and pamphlets are available free to the public.
   Educational packets for teachers are available upon request.
   Map of Rolla with directions to USGS Tours - You may tour Mid-Continent
   Mapping Center between the times of 8:00-11:00 a.m. and 12:30-3:00
   p.m., Monday through Friday. Walk-ins are welcome, but for groups of
   ten people or more, or for technical/special tours, please call in
   advance for scheduling. To schedule tours or classroom speakers,
   contact the MCMC Outreach office.
   For more information contact the Rolla ESIC office at:
   573-308-3500
   email: mcmcesic@usgs.gov
